      "<p>Triblio is a fun, fast-growing, and innovative company seeking a technically oriented team player to help our software development initiatives. Triblio's flagship product is a Codie award-winning marketing technology platform.  Our leadership team is comprised of highly successful and experienced technology executives with a proven track record of success.  We believe in a positive team culture, innovation, and a commitment to serving our customers.</p>\n<p>Role:\nThis position, reporting to the Chief Technology Officer (CTO), will work with our CTO and development team to contribute to all aspects of software development, including architecture, design, implementation, and testing.</p>\n<p>Key Responsibilities:\n-Design, write and test code for the Triblio’s software platform</p>\n<p>-Interact with team members to learn, refine and implement new capabilities</p>\n<p>-Assess, utilize, maintain and update development operational tools and frameworks</p>\n<p>-Maintain and enhance ongoing software product codebase</p>\n<p>-Collaborate with Product Management and Customer Success teams on technical issues</p>\n<p>Software Developer Requirements and Qualifications</p>\n<p>-Bachelor’s degree or higher in Computer Science or related field</p>\n<p>-Minimally 2 years experience in the design and implementation of browser-based applications and APIs</p>\n<p>-Familiarity with MVC</p>\n<p>-Hands-on experience with Javascript frameworks - React, Angular, NodeJ</p>\n<p>-Ability to learn and apply new technologies quickly</p>\n<p>-Ability to communicate and collaborate on technical projects with fellow developers</p>\n<p>-Strict attention to detail, highly organized and efficient</p>\n<p>-Strong written and verbal communication skills</p>\n<p>Must be able to commute to Reston, VA, however due to COVID Triblio staff currently works from home.</p>\n",
